            <title>[CASSANDRA-20523] Improve metadata log catch up with inter-DC mutation forwarding</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20523</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We currently try to catch up from the sender when we see a newer epoch in the message. If the message has been forwarded by a peer in the local DC it might not yet have caught up. We should always try to catch up from the originator of the message.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
